        "message": "Patch Set 10:\n\nOut of curiosity. How to run static code analysis during maven build, now, when \"analysis\" profile is removed? Does it run automatically with every build?",
        "patchset_number": 10
      },
      {
        "id": "32714640dca34ddadfb8bee08b9d91a1b70c0749",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2683,
          "name": "Piotr Jaszczyk",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "piotr.jaszczyk@nokia.com",
          "username": "jaszczur"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-08-16 08:49:20.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 10:\n\n@jakub - exactly. It is checked every time in maven's \"verify\" phase. This way every time you run mvn clean install you are checking the same things as Jenkins job. Hence, we can minimize impact on Jenkins workers - there will be less failing jobs (given authors will run build locally - my contribution in this MR is not a good example ;) ).",
